--------------------------------------------------------------------
Project structure walkthrough (for SME discussion)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
- src/main/java       -> application source code (controllers, services, main class)
- src/main/resources  -> configuration files (application.properties, static/, templates/)
- src/test/java       -> unit/integration test code
- SpringLearnApplication.java -> entry point; main() calls SpringApplication.run(),
  which bootstraps the Spring ApplicationContext, performs component scanning,
  auto-configures beans, and starts the embedded Tomcat server.
- @SpringBootApplication -> a convenience annotation combining:
    @Configuration      (marks class as a source of bean definitions)
    @EnableAutoConfiguration (enables Spring Boot's auto-configuration mechanism)
    @ComponentScan      (scans the package and sub-packages for components)
- pom.xml -> defines project metadata, parent (spring-boot-starter-parent),
  dependencies (spring-boot-starter-web, spring-boot-devtools, spring-boot-starter-test),
  and the spring-boot-maven-plugin used to build an executable jar.
  "Dependency Hierarchy" tab in Eclipse shows the full transitive dependency tree
  pulled in by each starter (e.g. spring-boot-starter-web pulls in Tomcat, Jackson,
  spring-webmvc, etc.)


